<h1>Music Teachers Wanted!</h1>

<h2>
Can you play the piano to at least AMEB Grade 8 or equivalent?<br/>
Do you have an outgoing personality?<br/>
Are you patient and good with children?<br/>
</h2>

<p>Yamaha, the Australian market leader in premium home entertainment, musical products, and music education is recruiting Music Teachers for our <strong>Melbourne, Geelong and Sydney Schools</strong>. </p>

<h2>What we’re looking for...</h2>

<ul>
	<li>Minimum Grade 8 AMEB Piano standard or equivalent </li>
	<li>Availability covering:
		<br/>-  Midweek 2 to 4 nights for 3 hours per night &amp;
		<br/>-  1 weekend day for 5hrs</li>
	<li>Good with children</li>
	<li>Self managing</li>
	<li>Good initiative, proactive style</li>
	<li>Responsible, reliable and punctual</li>
	<li>Flexible, open to new approach</li>
	<li>Outgoing and vivacious in a classroom environment</li>
	<li>Passionate musicians &amp; </li>
	<li>Comfortable singing voice</li>
</ul>

<h2>What you’re looking for...</h2>

<ul>
	<li>Full training provided over Dec ’06 – Jan ’07.</li>
	<li>A quality brand.</li>
	<li>Excellent pay.</li>
	<li>Consistent work.</li>
	<li>Further Opportunities!</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>There are currently 672,000 Yamaha students and over 20,000 Yamaha teachers worldwide</strong>. More information can be found here on <a href="default.asp">our website</a></p>

<h2>There is a 4 step interview process which will involve:</h2>
<ol>
	<li><strong>Phone Screen</strong>, then if required...</li>
	<li>Attend a <strong>Group Interview</strong> If you pass, visit...</li>
	<li><strong>A Yamaha Music Class</strong> (to see if this is for you) and if you like it attend a short...</li>
	<li><strong>Music Audition</strong> (to evaluate musical ability)</li>
</ol>

<p>Applications can be sent to teacher_vacancies@gmx.yamaha.com and should include a CV and letter outlining experience and how you meet our criteria. Applications close Friday 6 October 2006.</p>








